1. What is this Anti Blemish Mask used for?

It is used to support blemish-prone skin, reduce excess oil, refresh dull skin, and improve the look of uneven texture.

2. Can I use it daily?

No, use it 2–3 times a week or as per your skin’s comfort. Overusing masks may make the skin feel dry.

3. Does it help with acne and pimples?

It contains Neem Extract, Tea Tree Oil, Willow Bark Extract, and Basil Oil, which are commonly used in blemish-care routines.

4. Is it suitable for oily skin?

Yes, it is suitable for oily and blemish-prone skin as it helps control excess oil and purify the skin.

5. Can dry skin use this mask?

Yes, but use it less frequently and follow with a moisturizer, as blemish-care masks can sometimes feel drying.

6. How do I use this mask?

Apply an even layer on clean skin, avoid the eye area, leave it for the recommended time, then rinse off gently with water.










